Full Product Description: Allen Bradley offer a range of accessories and parts which are suitable for use with the MicroLogix family of PLCs, giving you full protection and a control system which is customised to meet your requirements. The MicroLogix controllers offer increased application coverage and superior network communications to keep your automated machine processes running smoothly.    Enable fast, easy PLC programming with the 2080-USBADAPTER by Allen Bradley.  The 2080-USBADAPTER is a USB Adapter Plug designed specifically for use with the Micro810 12-pt PLC. This device is required to connect to a PC for programming. The operating temperature for this adapter is -20 to 55 °C (-4 to 131 °F). It uses a USB Type A-B Male-Male connector.  The Micro810 smart relay micro programmable controller series is ideal for small applications, including temperature control, compressor control, and elevator control. It is the smallest PLC of the Micro800 family and can be conveniently personalised with plug-in modules to meet your specific needs. This cost-effective control solution features high current relay outputs (8A) which replace the need for external relays. The smart relay function blocks can be easily configured by the 1.5 LCD Display and Keypad. Programming is simple to do via the Connected Components Workbench software, which is free to download.      USB adapter plug for the Micro810 12-pt PLC  Snaps easily into the USB port on the control unit  Enables programming with the Connected Components Workbench software  Note: USB cable should not exceed 3m.      Programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) are complex computers which automate control processes by using programs to communicate electronic signals to machines and devices. In simplified terms, they are usually comprised of three components:A CPU (Central Processing Unit), which is the brain or processor of the system, Inputs, and Outputs. An input module detects signals from things like switches, sensors, and buttons. This is processed by the CPU, which leads to an output relaying the CPUs instructions to a machine or device. PLC system functions can be expanded by adding extra I/O modules. These devices are widely used in modern industrial automation for controlling machinery, in industries such as packaging, food and beverage production, pharmaceutical, and printing. Allen Bradley PLC systems provide dependable and flexible control capabilities at a fair price to give you seamless performance.

Full Product Description: The CR-U120AC2L pluggable interface relay is a univeral relay and is also commonly referred to as an ice cube relay. CR-U relays may be plugged into CR-U sockets and this combination of relay and socket may be seemlessly snap-on mounted onto a DIN Rail. CR-U relays have robust circular pin terminals, designed and manufactured to handle tough, repetitive-use applications and are more durable than standard relays.This relay operates with a 120 V AC rated control supply voltage and has a 2 c/o (SPDT) output with contacts rated at 250 V / 10 A, enabling the possibility of switching multiple circuits with a single input signal. The relay has an integrated test button which is used for the manual actuation of the relay by locking it's output contacts. The test button facilitates easy testing and commissioning. The relay also has an integrated LED, which provides the visual indication of the energization of the relay coil. Standard sockets, logic sockets, pluggable function modules, holders and markers are available as accessories.

Full Product Description: EtherNet - The 22-COMM-E EtherNet/IP adapter provides an internal EtherNet/IP connection for PowerFlex 40 drives. The adapter allows the drive to be controlled, configured, and data to be collected via an EtherNet/IP network. Web services are also provided and pages can be viewed with standard web browsers. The adapter also supports "Multi-Drive", a unique feature to Allen-Bradley. Multi-Drive allows up to five PowerFlex component class drives to connect to a single node on EtherNet/IP. Benefits include reduced hardware costs and a means to connect PowerFlex 4 drives to EtherNet/IP.  User configurable process display window  TCP/IP configuration (monitor only)  Email notification on fault, fault clear, and/or when the adapter takes its comm or idle fault actions  Monitoring device information, diagnostics and event queue  Direct launching of DriveExplorer or DriveExecutive on user's PC to connect on-line over EtherNet  DeviceNet - The PowerFlex 40 (not the PowerFlex 4) can be integrated with Allen-Bradley PLC Architectures using this optional DeviceNet communications module.  Network - The PowerFlex 70 can be integrated with PLC Architectures using these communications modules which fit neatly inside the PowerFlex 70.   A comms option cover is also needed for EtherNet & DeviceNet modules – choose the cover to match the PowerFlex 40 frame size (B or C).    Conveniently monitor industrial motor control systems with this communication adapter from Rockwell Automation's Allen Bradley range. It lets you collect, control and configure data on your PC (personal computer) over an ethernet or IP (internet protocol) network. The unit is internally mounted to a PowerFlex 40 AC drive to save space on a control panel. Its unique multi-drive feature lets you connect up to five PowerFlex drives to a single ethernet or IP node, which reduces hardware costs and helps simplify your communication system.    User-friendly configurable process-display window lets you choose your preferred view  Conveniently receive fault reports and other diagnostic information by email  Can be quickly and easily installed in the field  Configurable switches for enabling and disabling web pages and setting single or multi-drive modes      UL508C (Underwriters' Laboratories)  CSA(Canadian Standards Authority)  CE (Conformitè Europëenne)  EN (European Norm)      This device is able to transfer time-critical data that's necessary for controlling the PowerFlex drive, such as logic commands and status information, as well as feedback reports.
